= Kimodo Motion Generator =

#type: node
#context: sop
#tags: kimodo, motion, ai, kinefx, animation

Generates 3D human motion from a text prompt using NVIDIA Kimodo,
outputting a 77-joint SOMA skeleton compatible with Houdini KineFX.

== Overview ==

The Kimodo Motion Generator node connects to a locally running
[Kimodo|https://github.com/nv-tlabs/kimodo] inference server and
generates skeleton animation from a natural language description.

Press __Generate__ to send a POST request to the API server.
The resulting NPZ file is loaded and the skeleton is rebuilt on every
frame, driving 77 SOMA joints as points with `name`, `parent_id`, and
`localtransform` attributes.

== Quick Start ==

# Start the Docker services (text-encoder + api) as described in the README.
# Set __Prompt__ to describe the desired motion.
# Set __Duration__ in seconds.
# Press __Generate__. The node cooks automatically when the NPZ is ready.
# Set the Houdini frame range to match __Frame Count__ and play back.

Connect the output to a __Rig Pose SOP__ or any KineFX node that accepts
a packed skeleton with `localtransform`.

== Parameters ==

Server URL:
    URL of the running `kimodo_server` FastAPI service.
    Default: `http://localhost:8001`

Host Output Dir:
    The host-side directory mapped to `/workspace/output` inside Docker.
    Must contain `dev_reference.npz` when running in mock mode.

Prompt:
    Natural language description of the desired motion.
    Examples: "a person walks forward", "someone waves their hand".

Duration (s):
    Length of the generated motion in seconds. At 30 fps, 3 s = 90 frames.

Model:
    Kimodo model variant to use. Default: Kimodo-SOMA-RP-v1.1.

Generate:
    Sends a POST to `<Server URL>/generate` and writes the result path
    to __NPZ Path__. The node recooks automatically.

NPZ Path:
    Path to the NPZ file from the last Generate call.
    Can be set manually to load a pre-existing NPZ.

== Output Geometry ==

The node outputs one point per joint (77 total, SOMA skeleton):

table>>
    tr>>
        th>> Attribute
        th>> Type
        th>> Description
    tr>>
        td>> `name`
        td>> string
        td>> Joint name (e.g. Hips, LeftArm, RightFoot)
    tr>>
        td>> `parent_id`
        td>> int
        td>> Parent joint index; -1 for root (Hips)
    tr>>
        td>> `localtransform`
        td>> float[16]
        td>> Local rotation matrix + position (row-major 4x4)

== SOMA77 Skeleton Hierarchy ==

{{{
Hips (0)
  Spine1-Spine2-Chest
    Neck1-Neck2-Head-HeadEnd/Jaw/LeftEye/RightEye
    LeftShoulder-LeftArm-LeftForeArm-LeftHand  [+ fingers 15-38]
    RightShoulder-RightArm-RightForeArm-RightHand  [+ fingers 43-66]
  LeftLeg-LeftShin-LeftFoot-LeftToeBase-LeftToeEnd  [67-71]
  RightLeg-RightShin-RightFoot-RightToeBase-RightToeEnd  [72-76]
}}}

== Notes ==

* The node runs in __mock mode__ by default (returns dev_reference.npz
  without re-running inference). Set MOCK_MODE=0 in the Docker compose
  environment to enable live generation.
* Port 8000 is reserved by Docker Desktop on Windows; the API server runs
  on port __8001__ by default.
* Connect localtransform output to __Rig Pose SOP__ for KineFX rig binding.

